Newcastle United midfielder Moussa Sissoko has again spoken of his Arsenal ‘dream’ - but it would take an offer of more than £20million to trigger any deal before Monday night’s deadline.

The Magpies have made it known that they would only entertain a ‘ridiculous’ approach for their star player, with Arsenal, PSG and Liverpool all interested.

But in making that stance public, supporters fear they are courting such a sum. 

Moussa Sissoko joined Newcastle United from Ligue 1 side Toulouse in 2013 but could leave for a big fee

