‘Arsenal made me dream when I was a youngster. Patrick Vieira was my idol. I saw myself in him,’ he said.

‘For now, I'm a Newcastle player and I am happy at the club. I want to play in major competitions and I want to do it with this team.'

Newcastle left back Davide Santon is set to return to Inter Milan on loan for the remainder of the season, with a view to a permanent move, while the club look set to have missed out on the signature of Milton Keynes Dons youngster Dele Alli - who is at Tottenham Hotspur for a medical. 

